			<div class="blog-faq">
				<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>Is plastic surgery for men different from women?</h3>
					<p>Yes, there are important differences. Men have thicker skin, different muscle structures, and facial hair that influence surgical techniques. Male procedures are designed to preserve masculine features while achieving the desired improvement. Dr. Johar tailors each procedure specifically for the male anatomy.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>How long is the recovery for male plastic surgery?</h3>
					<p>Recovery time varies by procedure. Minor procedures like liposuction may require only three to five days of downtime, while more extensive procedures like facelifts may require two to three weeks. Dr. Johar provides a personalized recovery timeline during your consultation.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>Are the results of male plastic surgery natural-looking?</h3>
					<p>When performed by an experienced surgeon like Dr. Johar, results are designed to look completely natural. The goal is to enhance your features and create a refreshed appearance, not an artificial or "done" look. Many of our male patients report that colleagues notice they look better but cannot pinpoint the specific change.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>At what age should men consider plastic surgery?</h3>
					<p>There is no single "right" age for plastic surgery. The ideal age depends on the specific procedure and your individual concerns. Some procedures, like rhinoplasty, can be performed once facial growth is complete (typically in the late teens), while others, like facelifts, are more commonly performed on patients in their 40s and beyond.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>Will I have visible scars after male plastic surgery?</h3>
					<p>While all surgery leaves some scarring, Dr. Johar uses advanced techniques to minimize scar visibility. Incisions are typically placed in natural creases or hidden within the hairline. Over time, scars fade significantly and are usually barely noticeable.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>Can men combine multiple procedures?</h3>
					<p>Yes, many men choose to combine procedures to achieve their goals in a single surgery and recovery period. For example, combining liposuction with gynecomastia surgery, or facial procedures with a hair transplant. Dr. Johar will help you determine the safest and most effective approach during your consultation.</p>
				</div>
